The paper focuses on evaluating the vulnerability of processor caches to timing-based attacks, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also presents a new benchmark suite for testing cache designs, which involves software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL). Additionally, the paper discusses the implementation and evaluation of the benchmark suite on commodity processors, which involves computer architecture (cs.AR) and systems and control (cs.SY).
